    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "For what is worth, in https://github.com/jtimon/bitcoin/commits/jt (needs rebase on top of a backport of #7575, once it is merged) I'm considering that some callers may want to reimplement the method/function for caching the mediantime somehow (maybe some callers only cache the median time of the tip, I don't know). So, the way it is written, I don't see is as very disruptive to my libconsensus refactor plans (assuming anybody else apart from me cares about that branch at all), even if it looks incompatible with tiny steps I have proposed in the past like #6009.\n\nHaving said that, I don't have a strong opinion for bitcoin core one way or another. But some benchmarking to see if the extra memory is justifiable would certainly be useful to form an opinion.\n",
